  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "However, mixed feature extraction often ignores the dimensional difference, semantic gap and mutual interference between shape features and spatial coordinates.",
    "Therefore, Wang et al. (2022) proposed a new multi-feature guidance network (MFGNet) to overcome the inherent defects of mixed features.",
    "The network combines spatial coordinates and local features to guide the corresponding search.",
    "In contrast to the previous approach using mixed features, MFGNet consists of two distinct branches of matching computation: coordinate matching matrix computation and feature matching matrix computation.",
    "The two branch learning networks independently assign the correct correspondence."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Therefore, Wang et al. (2022) proposed a new multi-feature guidance network (MFGNet) to overcome the inherent defects of mixed features."
  ]
}